We’re stoked to share our new online workshop with you all! Over 25 years of experience, trial, error, highs, lows, smiles & frowns made this video possible. If you put a coil machine in your hand everyday at work, you should know this stuff. Enroll from anywhere on planet earth beginning Monday 1/23. Comment below with any questions or feel free to DM.  #KNOWYOURSHIT
TOMORROW @ 5pm PST 🗣️ Open Enrollment window opens for @sethciferri new online workshop “Build a Frame From Scratch”. Link in bio for more info 💥

It’s finally here. @sethciferri ‘s long awaited course that’ll show you the ins/outs of building a machine frame from scratch, with basic hand tools! He also covers how to wrap your own coils, along with some other must see TV. This workshop includes a live Q+A with Seth, we’re throwing in the past Q+A vault for FREE (over 60 hours with a value of $79) AND, anyone who pays in full gets entered into a drawing to win a liner or shader from Seth. Hi. Doing some spring cleaning and letting stuff go. I’ve got a few lots of acetates on my site @ tattoomachineshop.com right now, listing a few more later today, and getting back to making machines next week. Flatsides are finally happening. Thanks to those who’ve been so patient while I took a step back from building for a while.

Today I found out that I have way more acetate stencils than I’ll ever know what to do with, so I posted some of the ones I thought you’d like, on my website. I also found out today that I’ll be doing walk-in tattoos on Sundays at a cool little shop here in Portland. Shoot me a message if you’d like to get tattooed, and i’ll pass you the coordinates.
Thank you @catpartypetportraits for the lovely portrait of @therealdreamweasel and me. Greg looks magnificent.

**BENEFIT MACHINE AUCTION** 
Scroll through for pics - I bought this @mr_wrath liner for myself and it’s been quite the little ripper, but it’s time to give it up in favor of some loot sent to Gordon McCloud and his family, who lost everything in the fire. 
Highest bid wins the machine and all proceeds go to the  gofundme. Bids start @ 300$ 
#Gofundme link @jason_brooks_tattoo 
On Wednesday August 9, 2023, Gordon McCloud (aka WRATH in the world of tattooing), along with his wife and 3 children were victims of the catastrophic fires on Maui, Hawaii. Their town of Lahaina, along with their home and all earthly possessions were completely destroyed, leaving them homeless. Gordon has been an inspiration and paved the way for many in tattooing, as well as being very active and a volunteer in his community of Lahaina. He spends much of his time devoted to helping others, so let’s please help him and his family in their time of need. 100 percent of all funds raised will be sent directly to him, so he can help his family rebuild an entire life, possibly relocating off of Maui until Lahaina is rebuilt. All contributions are GREATLY appreciated! Thank you!!

Holy crap, I’m finally seeing a light at the end of the tunnel. Taking on a run of 50 machines turned out to be quite the endeavor, one that a much younger version of myself might have breezed through in a couple of weeks.  I’ve shipped out quite a few of them, and I’ve got a batch heading out tomorrow morning. Keep an eye out for tracking in your email, if you snagged one or two. 

That said, after all the math was done, balances settled up on, and tallies totaled, it turns out that I have TWELVE of these little dudes that aren’t spoken for. 
If you’ve sent me a deposit and we haven’t settled up, I have tried to reach you! Please reach out to me and claim your machine. If not, I’ll be refunding deposits and finding new homes for them. Thanks again and again. Y’all are the best.

On tonight’s episode of “my wife is out of town for several days” I’ll warm up old pizza with a heat gun in the workshop, where I’ve been for 18 hours. Brought to you by I haven’t showered since Wednesday, and Wellbutrin™️

Thought I’d finally share this experiment from about 7 years ago, using a torsion spring. I figured it would be nearly impossible to break a spring, and I had a number of different samples made with varying number of coils, and thickness of wire. The problem was stability, and I put it on the back burner, thinking I’d get around to figuring it out someday. It has excessive lateral flex, so I need to come up with a means of stabilizing the spring. I’ve tried using a pivot point that goes through the spring, but it’s still too wobbly. Maybe I’ll get back to it one of these days.

Yeah, already tried that. Lol 
(Re: my last post)
Experimental torsion spring machine 2017
Decided to go ahead and finish it. Runs better than I remembered

Genuine bootleg P. Rogers prefab liner. Literally handmade with a hacksaw, hand drill, and files, from scraps out of a big ol bucket of steel given to me a long time ago by @theeluckybastardpdx 

I made this frame for one of the MachineMachine videos, with no fixtures, no machine tools, and no measurements. So yeah, it’s a little wonky but it’s cool AF and runs freakin awesome. (Think 5/7/9/11) 
It’s 1/16” shorter than a standard height machine, so I had to make a set of cores for it. See that sweet old #spraguecapacitor ? This one’s got all the mojo and if anyone ever tries to question it’s authenticity, you can show them where it says #BOOTLEG right on the side plate. Oh yeah, and it’s pink. 500$

So here we are on Black Friday once again seems like it’s only been a year since the last one as part of the holiday tradition we’re doing a black Friday sale this time around is 35% off on any of our courses, starting tomorrow, Friday the 24th and it’s running till midnight on Monday the 27th. As an added bonus to the discount, anyone who makes any purchase will be entered to win a hand built tattoo machine that I made from a very limited run of flatside Supreme frames from Spaulding and Rogers. These frames were commissioned about a year and a half ago as part of a limited run, and I have a few of them left this one as special as it is unplated, and it’s virtually unheard of for a frame without plating to leave their factory. For some reason I was able to convince Bill Spaulding to work on this with me and I’m grateful for the opportunity. Another thing that makes this frame unique is the style of tube vise, and that the machining is done to facilitate the old Rogers “tube crusher“ style split collet. I’ve made the collet from a piece of tube grip, and it works very nicely. I wrapped these coils on 3/8 inch iron cores with 23 AWG magnet wire, and it hits very hard. So if someone out there is going to get this machine in the mail as a bonus when they sign up for any of our courses. Additionally, I’ve decided to give away two of these @wurth_usa hand punches. It’s the same punch I’ve been using for 20 years and swear by. You’re going to enter code BF23 at checkout when you go to www.machinemachine.co
